    "description": "The strategy trades XAUUSD (CFD) intraday to capture liquidity sweep and reversal behavior around major session windows, conditioning direction on higher timeframe trend. A 15 minute trend filter defines directional bias using a fast vs slow EMA crossover; only trades aligned with the prevailing bias are permitted. Within defined London and New York killzones (02:00 to 05:00 and 07:30 to 10:30 New York time), the strategy continuously marks a nearby liquidity level based on the most recent micro range: in buy bias it tracks the recent local bid low, and in sell bias it tracks the recent local bid high.\n\nExecution is on 1 minute bars and requires a two step pattern: first, price must sweep beyond the identified liquidity level and then close back through it (stop run and reclaim). Second, a confirmation candle must continue in the reversal direction by closing beyond the sweep candle extreme, at which point the strategy enters at market. Risk is defined by a stop at the sweep extreme and a fixed 2.0 reward to risk take profit. Position size is fixed via a lot based mapping, and trading is capped at one completed entry per day for the instrument with daily state reset.",
